[US trip self-maintenance cheat sheet, Windows and i.MX8, 2026-5]
... to be re-organized in description sequence.

1. Set up offline connection between Windows and i.MX8.
1.1 Preset i.MX8 with offline settings and boot up i.MX8.
1.2 Connect both machines through an RJ45 network cable.
1.2 Windows will bear an IP address such as 169.254.219.37.  i.MX8 should have been booted up with IP address 169.254.219.61 in the same network segment as preset in its offline configuration.
1.3 In Windows, open a browser.  Access the operation GUI of i.MX8 with its offline IP address, http://169.254.219.61:3000 .

2. ipLocator
This is suppposed to be executed in Windows to obtain the DHCP IP address of i.MX8 once i.MX8 boots up.
Double click ipLocator.bat and get the following results.  In the following scenario, Windows bears the DHCP IP address 172.16.14.28.  i.MX8 bears the DHCP IP address 172.16.14.61.

