2. Set wireless connection to DHCP AP through API
2.1 Given AP name and passphrase from on-site MIS administrator, e.g T-Global-4F-B-new, Tg2024091901.
2.1 Disconnect Windows network cable or wifi.  Set up offline operation of Windows and i.MX8.
2.2 Boot offline version of i.MX8.  Suppose the offline IP address is 169.254.219.61
2.3 In Windows, in the browser address bar, type http://169.254.219.61/set_wifi/<AP_name>/<passphrase> .  This will set up the wifi configuration to the mentioned AP.
2.4 Return from the offline version.  Set Windows back to DHCP and i.MX8 boots as online version.
2.5 Use ipLocator to obtain the newly assigned DHCP IP address of i.MX8, e.g. 172.16.14.61 .
2.6 In Windows, open a browser.  Access the operation GUI of i.MX8 with its DHCP IP address, http://172.16.14.61:3000

3. Set cabled connection to DHCP router.
3.1 Plug in a network cable from router/hub to Windows and boot the notebook/PC.
3.2 Plug in a network cable from router/hub to i.MX8 and boot i.MX8.
3.3 In Windows, click ipLocator to obtain the DHCP IP address of i.MX8, e.g. 172.16.14.61.
3.4 In Windows, open a browser.  Access the operation GUI of i.MX8 with its DHCP IP address, http://172.16.14.61:3000

